# gjoa-patch:
#   baseline-firefox: 151.0.1
#   touches:
#     - browser/app/profile/firefox.js
#
Default-pref a small set of gjoa-specific prefs at the firefox.js level
(omni.ja) so a fresh profile boots in gjoa's keyboard-first layout:

  sidebar.verticalTabs = true   — sidebar shows tabs vertically by default,
                                  matching the gjoa drawer / vim-style flow.
                                  Firefox's default (false) leaves tabs as a
                                  horizontal bar at top, which is what users
                                  saw on 2026-05-26 because we'd never
                                  overridden it.
  gjoa.sidebar.menuBar      = false   — no menu bar by default; sidebar covers it
  gjoa.toolbar.newTabButton = false   — no (+) button; keyboard does it

Users can flip any of these in about:config to restore native UI.

Eliminates two @media-pref CSS rules from chrome bundle (gjoa.uc.css)
that previously enforced the same defaults at chrome-load time.

diff --git a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
index edf96ae..53a047b 100644
--- a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
+++ b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
@@ -3609,3 +3609,11 @@ pref("browser.contentsharing.enabled", false);

 // Controls whether the "New" badge is shown on the content sharing menu items
 pref("browser.contentsharing.newBadge.enabled", true);
+
+// Gjoa: default chrome-UI prefs. Ship vertical-tabs ON (gjoa's whole
+// layout assumes the sidebar is the tab strip) and the menu/+button
+// hide-prefs OFF (sidebar covers their UX). Users can flip any of these
+// in about:config to restore the native UI.
+pref("sidebar.verticalTabs", true);
+pref("gjoa.sidebar.menuBar", false);
+pref("gjoa.toolbar.newTabButton", false);
